  <h1>MentalLift</h1>
  <p>Raising Awareness About Mental Health</p>
</header>
<main>
  <section>
    <h2>What is Mental Health?</h2>
    <p>Mental health includes our emotional, psychological, and social well-being. It affects how we think, feel, and act. It also helps determine how we handle stress, relate to others, and make choices.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why is Mental Health Important?</h2>
    <p>Good mental health is essential for living a balanced life. It helps us cope with the stresses of daily life, work productively, and build strong relationships.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Common Mental Health Issues</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Depression</li>
      <li>Anxiety Disorders</li>
      <li>Bipolar Disorder</li>
      <li>Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)</li>
      <li>Eating Disorders</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How to Take Care of Your Mental Health</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Talk openly about your feelings.</li>
      <li>Stay connected with friends and family.</li>
      <li>Practice regular physical activity.</li>
      <li>Get enough sleep.</li>
      <li>Seek professional help if needed.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Resources</h2>
    <p>If you or someone you know is struggling, here are some resources:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://www.mentalhealth.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MentalHealth.gov</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.nami.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NAMI - National Alliance on Mental Illness</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.who.int/mental_health/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">World Health Organization - Mental Health</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
